workout_explanation: This workout prioritizes compound movements for chest and triceps, followed by isolation exercises to fully target all muscle fibers. The volume and rep ranges are chosen to be manageable for an unknown fitness level within a 45-minute time constraint.  The exercise order is designed to maximize efficiency and minimize rest time.  The workout focuses on hypertrophy, using moderate weight and rep ranges to stimulate muscle growth.  The exercises are selected based on their effectiveness in targeting specific muscle groups and parts, and their suitability for progressive overload.  Alternatives are provided to allow for flexibility based on equipment availability and individual preferences.
